# Frontend SPA rules

- The frontend is a plain HTML/CSS/JavaScript SPA with client-side routing; do not introduce a framework unless the repo docs are updated and the choice is approved.
- Keep URLs bookmarkable and use them for dashboard/search view state.
- Treat backend authorization as the source of truth; the UI must not assume access from local state alone.
- Viewers may use temporary filters and bookmarked URLs, but cannot save dashboard changes.
- Keep UI modules separated into routes/views, reusable components, and API/state helpers.
- Prefer accessible form controls, clear error states, and obvious domain-context labeling in dashboards and admin screens.
